        <descriptionSet>
            <description>This rare and historically important album contains objects, mostly locks of hair, belonging to members of the Bourbon royal family of France assembled during the era of the Restoration (1814-30).  Snippets of hair, here treated almost as holy relics, were the most common objectified form of sentimental remembrance in nineteenth-century Europe. The objects were collected by Madame de Clérambault, lady-in-waiting to the duchess of Berry, daughter-in-law of King Charles X (reigned 1824-30).  </description>
